00:00:00.256 --> 00:00:03.072
<b>Using Safety In Motion helps protect your body.</b>

00:00:03.584 --> 00:00:05.888
<b>Improving leg strength and balance is important</b>

00:00:06.400 --> 00:00:08.348
<b>You have learned that your risk is high</b>

00:00:08.393 --> 00:00:12.392
<b>when the center of your chest is no longer over </b>
<b>your line of strength and balance.</b>

00:00:12.544 --> 00:00:14.336
<b>But your risk is very high</b>

00:00:14.592 --> 00:00:16.384
<b>if you are also twisting and bending.</b>

00:00:16.896 --> 00:00:18.768
<b>If you see or experience this,</b>

00:00:18.944 --> 00:00:19.712
<b>stop and think</b>

00:00:20.224 --> 00:00:21.760
<b>How can I do this a better way?</b>

00:00:22.528 --> 00:00:23.040
<b>Remember,</b>

00:00:23.296 --> 00:00:25.344
<b>reaching with your Same Side Hand and Foot</b>

00:00:25.600 --> 00:00:26.624
<b>and pointing your toe</b>

00:00:26.880 --> 00:00:28.048
<b>reduces the stress</b>

00:00:28.160 --> 00:00:29.388
<b>and improves your balance.</b>

